threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib/ld-uClibc.so.0, with debug_info, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a sophisticated Mirai-style IoT botnet designed for ARMv7 architectures. It exhibits definitive malicious behaviors including: 1) Persistence via modification of '/etc/rc.local' and '/etc/init.d/sysd', often self-replicating as '/usr/bin/.sh'; 2) Evasion through process name spoofing (using 'prctl' to appear as 'kworker', 'ntpd', or 'sshd') and 'hide_pid' logic; 3) A 'killer' module (killer_main, killer_tcp) that scans '/proc' to terminate competing malware processes; 4) Multiple DDoS attack vectors including HTTP floods with Cloudflare bypass, UDP floods, and VSE floods; and 5) Remote command-and-control functionality with an update mechanism (handle_update) using 'wget', 'curl', and 'tftp' to fetch payloads.
